You can do this by using a OncePerRequestFilter:

    @Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE)
    @Component
    public class CorrelationIdFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {
        @Override
        protected void doFilterInternal(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response,
          FilterChain filterChain) throws ServletException, IOException {
            try {
                var id = UUID.randomUUID().toString();
                response.addHeader(&quot;correlation-id&quot;, id);
                MDC.put(&quot;correlation-id&quot;, id);
                filterChain.doFilter(request, response);
            } finally {
                MDC.remove(&quot;correlation-id&quot;);
            }  
        }
    }


Important is the order that it is actually happening as the first filter.

Also you can add the correlation id to the mdc so its added to all the logs aswell.

Please let me know if this works, as adding a header is apparently depending on the version of spring you are using.

Here&#39;s how I do it:

1- As mentioned by @Loading, you can do this by using a OncePerRequestFilter:

````
public class MDCFilter extends OncePerRequestFilter {
    private final String X_REQUEST_ID = &quot;X-Request-ID&quot;;
    private final String MDC_KEY = &quot;UUID&quot;;

    @Override
    protected void doFilterInternal(final HttpServletRequest request, final HttpServletResponse response,
            final FilterChain chain)
            throws java.io.IOException, ServletException {
        try {
            final String uuid;
            if (!StringUtils.isEmpty(request.getHeader(X_REQUEST_ID))) {
                uuid = request.getHeader(X_REQUEST_ID);
            } else {
                uuid = UUID.randomUUID().toString().toUpperCase().replace(&quot;-&quot;, &quot;&quot;);
            }

            MDC.put(MDC_KEY, uuid);
            response.addHeader(X_REQUEST_ID, uuid);

            chain.doFilter(request, response);
        } finally {
            MDC.remove(MDC_KEY);
        }
    }
}
````

It allows the client to have their own &quot;X-Request-ID&quot;. if client doesn&#39;t provide it, it will be assigned.

2- In a @Configuration class, add this bean:
````
 @Bean
    public FilterRegistrationBean&lt;MDCFilter&gt; servletRegistrationBean() {
        FilterRegistrationBean&lt;MDCFilter&gt; registrationBean = new FilterRegistrationBean&lt;&gt;();
        MDCFilter mdcFilter = new MDCFilter();
        registrationBean.setFilter(mdcFilter);
        registrationBean.setOrder(2);
        return registrationBean;
    }
````
- Additional things you can do:

- Utilize it for logging:
````
&lt;pattern&gt;%-5level| %t | [%X{UUID:-application}] | %logger{36} | %m %n&lt;/pattern&gt;
```` 

- Utilize it for internal API calls:
````
.header(&quot;X-Request-ID&quot;, MDC.get(&quot;UUID&quot;))
````

